---
title: Garlic Confit (Cast Iron)
servings: 4
tags: [condiment, garlic, oven, confit, cast iron]
prep_time: 5 minutes
cook_time: 45 minutes
---

-- Preheat oven to 300°F.

Place @garlic{}(cloves separated and peeled; quantity as desired) in a #small cast-iron pan{}. Cover completely with @olive oil{}.

Roast at 300°F for ~{30-60%minutes}, depending on the amount of garlic, until cloves are completely tender and lightly golden.
